TOPIC: Docker Advanced in Practical Way ( Using REST APIs )

Level:
    Intermediate

Assumptions:
    1. Docker Installation
    2. Basic Understanding of Dockers and its Commands

Sub-Topics:
    1. REST ( Representational state transfer ) API ? -->

        a)  REST is a concept, an architectural style which may use HTTP, FTP or other communication protocols but is widely used with HTTP.
        b)  REST is the way HTTP should be used.
        c)  REST API is an application program interface (API) that uses HTTP ( in most cases ) requests to GET, PUT, POST and DELETE data.


    2. Run Docker commands using REST APIs.

        a) List Images
        b) List Containers
        c) Start Container
        d) Run Specific command inside container
